algorithm_technique: Sort boxes descending. Use two pointers on warehouse, greedily placing largest boxes into smallest available openings from either end.
problem_summary_simple: Fit the maximum number of boxes into warehouse rooms, pushing from either side.
problem_summary_technical: Greedily match sorted boxes to warehouse openings by considering placement from both left and right ends.
key_insights: Sorting boxes in descending order is key to the greedy strategy.
The ability to push from either side means we can utilize the smallest available room height from either end.
This problem is a variation of the first, with the added flexibility of two-sided entry.
